// EBIOS RM — descriptions des mesures ANSSI et ISO 27001 (FR + EN)
// Chargé automatiquement à l'ouverture de l'onglet Socle
window.EBIOS_DESCRIPTIONS = {anssi: {"1": "Organiser des formations r\u00e9guli\u00e8res en s\u00e9curit\u00e9 des SI pour les \u00e9quipes techniques (administrateurs, d\u00e9veloppeurs, op\u00e9rateurs). Couvrir les menaces actuelles, les outils de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 et les proc\u00e9dures internes.", "2": "Mettre en place des actions de sensibilisation p\u00e9riodiques pour tous les collaborateurs : reconnaissance du phishing, gestion des mots de passe, signalement des incidents, utilisation des ressources informatiques.", "3": "Maintenir une cartographie \u00e0 jour du SI : r\u00e9seaux, syst\u00e8mes, applications, flux de donn\u00e9es. La r\u00e9viser \u00e0 chaque \u00e9volution significative et la prot\u00e9ger en confidentialit\u00e9.", "4": "Tenir un inventaire exhaustif et \u00e0 jour de tous les actifs mat\u00e9riels et logiciels. Attribuer un propri\u00e9taire responsable \u00e0 chaque actif.", "5": "D\u00e9finir des niveaux de classification de l'information (ex. public, interne, confidentiel, secret). Identifier les serveurs h\u00e9bergeant les donn\u00e9es les plus sensibles et appliquer des mesures de protection renforc\u00e9es.", "6": "Recenser tous les comptes \u00e0 privil\u00e8ges (administrateurs locaux, de domaine, de service, applicatifs). Auditer et \u00e9purer r\u00e9guli\u00e8rement cet inventaire ; supprimer les comptes obsol\u00e8tes.", "7": "Formaliser et appliquer des proc\u00e9dures de gestion des acc\u00e8s lors des arriv\u00e9es (cr\u00e9ation de comptes), mutations (mise \u00e0 jour des droits) et d\u00e9parts (suppression des acc\u00e8s, r\u00e9cup\u00e9ration du mat\u00e9riel).", "8": "Restreindre l'acc\u00e8s aux interfaces et outils d'administration aux seuls personnels formellement habilit\u00e9s. Maintenir une liste d'habilitations et la r\u00e9viser r\u00e9guli\u00e8rement.", "9": "D\u00e9finir une politique de mots de passe (longueur minimale \u2265 12 caract\u00e8res, complexit\u00e9, renouvellement, historique) et la faire respecter techniquement sur tous les syst\u00e8mes.", "10": "Ne jamais stocker les mots de passe en clair. Utiliser des fonctions de hachage robustes avec sel (bcrypt, Argon2, PBKDF2). Auditer r\u00e9guli\u00e8rement les bases d'authentification.", "11": "D\u00e9ployer l'authentification multi-facteurs (MFA) pour les acc\u00e8s aux ressources critiques, les comptes \u00e0 privil\u00e8ges et tous les acc\u00e8s distants au SI.", "12": "Interdire la pr\u00e9sence de mots de passe en clair dans les fichiers de configuration, scripts, code source ou bases de donn\u00e9es. Utiliser des coffres-forts de secrets.", "13": "Modifier syst\u00e9matiquement les identifiants et mots de passe livr\u00e9s par d\u00e9faut sur tous les \u00e9quipements r\u00e9seau, serveurs, applications et bases de donn\u00e9es avant leur mise en service.", "14": "Centraliser l'authentification via un annuaire (Active Directory, LDAP, SSO) pour r\u00e9duire la prolif\u00e9ration des comptes locaux et faciliter la gestion des droits.", "15": "Appliquer le principe du moindre privil\u00e8ge : n'attribuer \u00e0 chaque utilisateur, application ou service que les droits strictement n\u00e9cessaires \u00e0 ses fonctions. R\u00e9viser les droits r\u00e9guli\u00e8rement.", "16": "Appliquer les mises \u00e0 jour de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 sur tous les logiciels (OS, navigateurs, plugins, applications m\u00e9tier) dans des d\u00e9lais adapt\u00e9s \u00e0 la criticit\u00e9 des vuln\u00e9rabilit\u00e9s.", "17": "D\u00e9finir et appliquer une configuration de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 de base (benchmark CIS ou \u00e9quivalent) sur tous les postes de travail : d\u00e9sactivation des services inutiles, activation du pare-feu local, chiffrement de disque.", "18": "Chiffrer les donn\u00e9es sensibles stock\u00e9es sur les postes de travail (BitLocker, FileVault ou \u00e9quivalent). Prot\u00e9ger les cl\u00e9s de chiffrement par un m\u00e9canisme appropri\u00e9.", "19": "D\u00e9ployer et maintenir \u00e0 jour une solution de protection contre les codes malveillants (antivirus, EDR) sur l'ensemble du parc. Activer la supervision centralis\u00e9e des alertes.", "20": "D\u00e9finir une politique d'utilisation des supports amovibles : interdire les supports non autoris\u00e9s, contr\u00f4ler les transferts, scanner les supports externes avant usage.", "21": "Segmenter le r\u00e9seau en zones de confiance (DMZ, r\u00e9seau d'administration, r\u00e9seau utilisateurs, OT\u2026) et filtrer les flux inter-zones par des pare-feux ou ACL selon le principe du besoin d'en conna\u00eetre.", "22": "Utiliser WPA2-Enterprise ou WPA3 pour les r\u00e9seaux Wi-Fi professionnels. Isoler les r\u00e9seaux Wi-Fi invit\u00e9s du r\u00e9seau interne. D\u00e9sactiver les protocoles obsol\u00e8tes (WEP, WPA).", "23": "Bannir les protocoles non chiffr\u00e9s (Telnet, FTP, HTTP, SNMPv1/v2) et les remplacer par leurs \u00e9quivalents s\u00e9curis\u00e9s (SSH, SFTP/FTPS, HTTPS, SNMPv3).", "24": "Mettre en place un proxy filtrant, un pare-feu applicatif et une protection antivirale en passerelle pour superviser et filtrer les flux Internet entrants et sortants.", "25": "Encadrer contractuellement et techniquement les interconnexions avec les partenaires : VPN chiffr\u00e9, authentification forte, flux limit\u00e9s au strict n\u00e9cessaire, supervision et audit r\u00e9gulier.", "26": "Encadrer les acc\u00e8s distants par VPN avec authentification forte (MFA). Journaliser toutes les sessions. R\u00e9viser r\u00e9guli\u00e8rement les droits d'acc\u00e8s distants et r\u00e9voquer les acc\u00e8s inutilis\u00e9s.", "27": "D\u00e9ployer une solution de supervision des flux r\u00e9seaux (SIEM, IDS/IPS, NetFlow) pour d\u00e9tecter les comportements anormaux, les exfiltrations de donn\u00e9es et les tentatives d'intrusion.", "28": "Utiliser des postes d\u00e9di\u00e9s exclusivement aux t\u00e2ches d'administration, sans acc\u00e8s \u00e0 Internet ni \u00e0 la messagerie bureautique. Ces postes ne doivent pas \u00eatre utilis\u00e9s pour des activit\u00e9s courantes.", "29": "Restreindre et s\u00e9curiser les outils de prise en main \u00e0 distance (RDP, SSH, outils tiers) : acc\u00e8s limit\u00e9 aux seuls administrateurs habilit\u00e9s, chiffrement fort, journalisation, MFA.", "30": "Isoler le r\u00e9seau d'administration dans un VLAN ou segment d\u00e9di\u00e9, s\u00e9par\u00e9 physiquement ou logiquement des r\u00e9seaux utilisateurs et accessibles uniquement depuis les postes d'administration.", "31": "Activer la journalisation de toutes les op\u00e9rations d'administration (connexions, commandes, modifications de configuration). Conserver les logs dans un espace s\u00e9curis\u00e9 en int\u00e9grit\u00e9.", "32": "Accorder les droits d'administration au strict minimum n\u00e9cessaire. Recourir \u00e0 l'\u00e9l\u00e9vation de privil\u00e8ges temporaire (sudo, PAM) plut\u00f4t qu'\u00e0 des comptes permanents \u00e0 hauts privil\u00e8ges.", "33": "Prot\u00e9ger les \u00e9quipements nomades contre la perte et le vol : c\u00e2ble antivol, d\u00e9marrage prot\u00e9g\u00e9 par mot de passe, chiffrement de disque activ\u00e9, proc\u00e9dure de signalement de perte.", "34": "Chiffrer int\u00e9gralement le disque des terminaux nomades (BitLocker, FileVault, VeraCrypt). S'assurer que le chiffrement est actif avant toute utilisation hors des locaux.", "35": "Imposer l'utilisation d'un VPN d'entreprise pour tout acc\u00e8s au SI depuis l'ext\u00e9rieur. D\u00e9sactiver les connexions directes sans VPN. Contr\u00f4ler la conformit\u00e9 du poste avant connexion (NAC).", "36": "D\u00e9finir une politique formelle de mise \u00e0 jour pr\u00e9cisant les d\u00e9lais d'application selon le niveau de criticit\u00e9 (CVSS \u2265 9 : < 72h, CVSS 7-9 : < 7j, autres : < 30j) et les proc\u00e9dures de test.", "37": "Identifier les logiciels et syst\u00e8mes en fin de vie (EOL/EOS). Planifier et budg\u00e9ter la migration avant la fin du support \u00e9diteur. Isoler les syst\u00e8mes non migrables dans l'attente.", "38": "Appliquer les correctifs de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 critiques dans les d\u00e9lais d\u00e9finis par la politique de mise \u00e0 jour. Mettre en place un processus de patch management avec test, d\u00e9ploiement et v\u00e9rification.", "39": "Activer et centraliser les journaux des \u00e9quipements critiques (AD, pare-feux, serveurs, applications). D\u00e9finir la dur\u00e9e de r\u00e9tention (\u2265 1 an recommand\u00e9). Prot\u00e9ger les logs en int\u00e9grit\u00e9.", "40": "D\u00e9finir et appliquer une politique de sauvegarde (r\u00e8gle 3-2-1 : 3 copies, 2 supports diff\u00e9rents, 1 hors-site). Tester r\u00e9guli\u00e8rement les restaurations. Prot\u00e9ger les sauvegardes contre les ransomwares.", "41": "R\u00e9aliser des audits de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 r\u00e9guliers (tests d'intrusion, revues de configuration, audits de code) par des prestataires qualifi\u00e9s PASSI. Suivre et traiter les vuln\u00e9rabilit\u00e9s identifi\u00e9es.", "42": "D\u00e9signer officiellement un r\u00e9f\u00e9rent ou RSSI charg\u00e9 de la s\u00e9curit\u00e9 des SI. D\u00e9finir son p\u00e9rim\u00e8tre de responsabilit\u00e9s, lui allouer les ressources n\u00e9cessaires et le faire conna\u00eetre de tous les collaborateurs."}, iso: {"4.1": "L'organisation doit d\u00e9terminer les enjeux externes et internes pertinents par rapport \u00e0 sa finalit\u00e9 et qui influent sur sa capacit\u00e9 \u00e0 obtenir les r\u00e9sultats attendus de son SMSI.", "4.2": "L'organisation doit d\u00e9terminer les parties int\u00e9ress\u00e9es qui sont pertinentes dans le cadre du SMSI et les exigences de ces parties int\u00e9ress\u00e9es.", "4.3": "L'organisation doit d\u00e9terminer les limites et l'applicabilit\u00e9 du SMSI afin d'\u00e9tablir son domaine d'application, en tenant compte des enjeux, des exigences et des interfaces.", "4.4": "L'organisation doit \u00e9tablir, mettre en \u0153uvre, tenir \u00e0 jour et am\u00e9liorer en continu un syst\u00e8me de management de la s\u00e9curit\u00e9 de l'information, y compris les processus n\u00e9cessaires et leurs interactions.", "5.1": "La direction doit faire preuve de leadership et d'engagement vis-\u00e0-vis du SMSI : d\u00e9finir la politique, s'assurer de l'int\u00e9gration dans les processus m\u00e9tier, fournir les ressources, communiquer l'importance.", "5.2": "La direction doit \u00e9tablir une politique de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 de l'information appropri\u00e9e, incluant des objectifs, un engagement de conformit\u00e9 et d'am\u00e9lioration continue. Elle doit \u00eatre document\u00e9e, communiqu\u00e9e et disponible.", "5.3": "La direction doit s'assurer que les responsabilit\u00e9s et autorit\u00e9s des r\u00f4les pertinents pour la s\u00e9curit\u00e9 de l'information sont attribu\u00e9es et communiqu\u00e9es au sein de l'organisation.", "6.1.1": "Lors de la planification du SMSI, l'organisation doit d\u00e9terminer les risques et opportunit\u00e9s \u00e0 prendre en compte pour s'assurer que le SMSI peut atteindre les r\u00e9sultats escompt\u00e9s.", "6.1.2": "L'organisation doit d\u00e9finir et appliquer un processus d'appr\u00e9ciation des risques de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 de l'information : crit\u00e8res d'acceptation, m\u00e9thodologie reproductible, identification, analyse et \u00e9valuation des risques.", "6.1.3": "L'organisation doit d\u00e9finir et appliquer un processus de traitement des risques de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 : s\u00e9lectionner les options de traitement, d\u00e9terminer les mesures n\u00e9cessaires, produire une d\u00e9claration d'applicabilit\u00e9.", "6.2": "L'organisation doit \u00e9tablir des objectifs de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 de l'information aux fonctions et niveaux pertinents. Ils doivent \u00eatre mesurables, coh\u00e9rents avec la politique, communiqu\u00e9s et mis \u00e0 jour.", "6.3": "Lorsque l'organisation d\u00e9termine le besoin de modifications du SMSI, celles-ci doivent \u00eatre planifi\u00e9es et r\u00e9alis\u00e9es de mani\u00e8re ma\u00eetris\u00e9e.", "7.1": "L'organisation doit identifier et fournir les ressources n\u00e9cessaires \u00e0 l'\u00e9tablissement, la mise en \u0153uvre, la tenue \u00e0 jour et l'am\u00e9lioration continue du SMSI.", "7.2": "L'organisation doit d\u00e9terminer les comp\u00e9tences n\u00e9cessaires des personnes effectuant un travail ayant une incidence sur la s\u00e9curit\u00e9 de l'information, s'assurer qu'elles sont comp\u00e9tentes et conserver les preuves.", "7.3": "Les personnes effectuant un travail sous le contr\u00f4le de l'organisation doivent \u00eatre sensibilis\u00e9es \u00e0 la politique de s\u00e9curit\u00e9, \u00e0 leur contribution \u00e0 l'efficacit\u00e9 du SMSI et aux cons\u00e9quences de la non-conformit\u00e9.", "7.4": "L'organisation doit d\u00e9terminer les besoins de communication interne et externe pertinents pour le SMSI : quoi communiquer, quand, \u00e0 qui, comment.", "7.5.1": "Le SMSI de l'organisation doit inclure les informations document\u00e9es exig\u00e9es par la norme et celles jug\u00e9es n\u00e9cessaires \u00e0 l'efficacit\u00e9 du SMSI.", "7.5.2": "Lors de la cr\u00e9ation et de la mise \u00e0 jour des informations document\u00e9es, l'organisation doit s'assurer de l'identification, du format, de la revue et de l'approbation appropri\u00e9s.", "7.5.3": "Les informations document\u00e9es doivent \u00eatre ma\u00eetris\u00e9es pour s'assurer qu'elles sont disponibles, ad\u00e9quatement prot\u00e9g\u00e9es, distribu\u00e9es, stock\u00e9es, conserv\u00e9es et \u00e9limin\u00e9es de mani\u00e8re appropri\u00e9e.", "8.1": "L'organisation doit planifier, mettre en \u0153uvre et ma\u00eetriser les processus n\u00e9cessaires pour satisfaire aux exigences de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 de l'information et r\u00e9aliser les actions d\u00e9termin\u00e9es dans la planification.", "8.2": "L'organisation doit r\u00e9aliser des appr\u00e9ciations des risques de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 de l'information \u00e0 des intervalles planifi\u00e9s ou lorsque des changements significatifs sont propos\u00e9s ou surviennent.", "8.3": "L'organisation doit mettre en \u0153uvre le plan de traitement des risques de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 de l'information et conserver les informations document\u00e9es sur les r\u00e9sultats du traitement.", "9.1": "L'organisation doit \u00e9valuer les performances de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 de l'information et l'efficacit\u00e9 du SMSI : d\u00e9terminer ce qu'il faut surveiller et mesurer, les m\u00e9thodes, la fr\u00e9quence et les responsabilit\u00e9s.", "9.2": "L'organisation doit r\u00e9aliser des audits internes \u00e0 des intervalles planifi\u00e9s pour fournir des informations sur la conformit\u00e9 du SMSI aux exigences propres et \u00e0 la norme.", "9.3": "La direction doit, \u00e0 des intervalles planifi\u00e9s, proc\u00e9der \u00e0 la revue du SMSI pour s'assurer qu'il est toujours pertinent, ad\u00e9quat et efficace.", "10.1": "L'organisation doit am\u00e9liorer en continu la pertinence, l'ad\u00e9quation et l'efficacit\u00e9 du SMSI.", "10.2": "Lorsqu'une non-conformit\u00e9 se produit, l'organisation doit r\u00e9agir, \u00e9valuer les actions n\u00e9cessaires pour en \u00e9liminer la cause, mettre en \u0153uvre les actions correctives et en v\u00e9rifier l'efficacit\u00e9.", "A.5.1": "Des politiques de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 de l'information, approuv\u00e9es par la direction, publi\u00e9es, communiqu\u00e9es au personnel concern\u00e9 et aux parties int\u00e9ress\u00e9es, doivent \u00eatre d\u00e9finies, r\u00e9vis\u00e9es \u00e0 intervalles planifi\u00e9s.", "A.5.2": "Les responsabilit\u00e9s en mati\u00e8re de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 de l'information doivent \u00eatre d\u00e9finies et attribu\u00e9es conform\u00e9ment aux politiques \u00e9tablies.", "A.5.3": "Les t\u00e2ches et domaines de responsabilit\u00e9 conflictuels doivent \u00eatre s\u00e9par\u00e9s pour r\u00e9duire les risques de modification ou d'utilisation non autoris\u00e9e des actifs.", "A.5.4": "La direction doit exiger de l'ensemble du personnel d'appliquer la s\u00e9curit\u00e9 de l'information conform\u00e9ment aux politiques, r\u00e8gles et proc\u00e9dures \u00e9tablies.", "A.5.5": "Des relations appropri\u00e9es avec les autorit\u00e9s comp\u00e9tentes (r\u00e9gulateurs, forces de l'ordre, pompiers, etc.) doivent \u00eatre \u00e9tablies et maintenues.", "A.5.6": "Des relations appropri\u00e9es avec des groupes ou forums sp\u00e9cialis\u00e9s en s\u00e9curit\u00e9 de l'information et des associations professionnelles doivent \u00eatre \u00e9tablies et maintenues.", "A.5.7": "Des informations relatives aux menaces pesant sur la s\u00e9curit\u00e9 de l'information doivent \u00eatre recueillies et analys\u00e9es pour am\u00e9liorer les mesures de protection.", "A.5.8": "La s\u00e9curit\u00e9 de l'information doit \u00eatre int\u00e9gr\u00e9e dans la gestion de projet tout au long du cycle de vie du projet.", "A.5.9": "Un inventaire des informations et autres actifs associ\u00e9s, y compris leurs propri\u00e9taires, doit \u00eatre \u00e9tabli et tenu \u00e0 jour.", "A.5.10": "Des r\u00e8gles relatives \u00e0 l'utilisation correcte et \u00e0 la gestion des informations et autres actifs associ\u00e9s doivent \u00eatre identifi\u00e9es, document\u00e9es et mises en \u0153uvre.", "A.5.11": "Le personnel et les autres parties int\u00e9ress\u00e9es doivent restituer tous les actifs appartenant \u00e0 l'organisation \u00e0 la fin de leur contrat, accord ou engagement.", "A.5.12": "L'information doit \u00eatre classifi\u00e9e selon les exigences l\u00e9gales, la valeur, la criticit\u00e9 et la sensibilit\u00e9 vis-\u00e0-vis d'une divulgation ou modification non autoris\u00e9e.", "A.5.13": "Un ensemble appropri\u00e9 de proc\u00e9dures de marquage de l'information doit \u00eatre \u00e9labor\u00e9 et mis en \u0153uvre conform\u00e9ment au sch\u00e9ma de classification.", "A.5.14": "Des r\u00e8gles, proc\u00e9dures ou accords de transfert d'information doivent \u00eatre en place pour tous les types de moyens de transfert au sein de l'organisation et avec les parties ext\u00e9rieures.", "A.5.15": "Des r\u00e8gles de contr\u00f4le d'acc\u00e8s logique et physique aux informations et actifs doivent \u00eatre \u00e9tablies et mises en \u0153uvre sur la base des exigences m\u00e9tier et de s\u00e9curit\u00e9.", "A.5.16": "Le cycle de vie complet des identit\u00e9s doit \u00eatre g\u00e9r\u00e9, de la cr\u00e9ation \u00e0 la suppression, selon les processus d\u00e9finis.", "A.5.17": "L'attribution et la gestion des informations d'authentification secr\u00e8tes doivent \u00eatre contr\u00f4l\u00e9es par un processus formel.", "A.5.18": "Les droits d'acc\u00e8s aux informations et actifs doivent \u00eatre provisionn\u00e9s, revus, modifi\u00e9s et supprim\u00e9s conform\u00e9ment \u00e0 la politique de contr\u00f4le d'acc\u00e8s.", "A.5.19": "Des processus et proc\u00e9dures doivent \u00eatre d\u00e9finis et mis en \u0153uvre pour g\u00e9rer les risques de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 de l'information li\u00e9s \u00e0 l'utilisation des produits ou services des fournisseurs.", "A.5.20": "Les exigences de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 pertinentes doivent \u00eatre \u00e9tablies et convenues avec chaque fournisseur, selon le type de relation.", "A.5.21": "Des processus et proc\u00e9dures doivent \u00eatre d\u00e9finis et mis en \u0153uvre pour g\u00e9rer les risques li\u00e9s \u00e0 la cha\u00eene d'approvisionnement en produits et services TIC.", "A.5.22": "L'organisation doit surveiller, revoir et auditer r\u00e9guli\u00e8rement les pratiques de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 des fournisseurs et la prestation de services.", "A.5.23": "Les processus d'acquisition, d'utilisation, de gestion et de sortie des services en nuage (cloud) doivent \u00eatre d\u00e9finis conform\u00e9ment aux exigences de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 de l'information.", "A.5.24": "L'organisation doit planifier et se pr\u00e9parer \u00e0 g\u00e9rer les incidents de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 de l'information en d\u00e9finissant, \u00e9tablissant et communiquant des processus, r\u00f4les et responsabilit\u00e9s.", "A.5.25": "L'organisation doit \u00e9valuer les \u00e9v\u00e9nements de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 de l'information et d\u00e9cider s'ils doivent \u00eatre classifi\u00e9s comme incidents.", "A.5.26": "Les incidents de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 doivent \u00eatre trait\u00e9s conform\u00e9ment aux proc\u00e9dures document\u00e9es.", "A.5.27": "Les connaissances acquises des incidents de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 doivent \u00eatre utilis\u00e9es pour renforcer et am\u00e9liorer les mesures de s\u00e9curit\u00e9.", "A.5.28": "L'organisation doit \u00e9tablir et mettre en \u0153uvre des proc\u00e9dures d'identification, de collecte, d'acquisition et de pr\u00e9servation des preuves relatives aux incidents.", "A.5.29": "L'organisation doit planifier le maintien de la s\u00e9curit\u00e9 de l'information \u00e0 un niveau appropri\u00e9 pendant une perturbation.", "A.5.30": "La pr\u00e9paration TIC pour la continuit\u00e9 de l'activit\u00e9 doit \u00eatre planifi\u00e9e, mise en \u0153uvre, maintenue et test\u00e9e sur la base des plans de continuit\u00e9.", "A.5.31": "Les exigences l\u00e9gales, r\u00e9glementaires, contractuelles et autres exigences pertinentes relatives \u00e0 la s\u00e9curit\u00e9 de l'information doivent \u00eatre identifi\u00e9es et document\u00e9es.", "A.5.32": "Des proc\u00e9dures appropri\u00e9es pour prot\u00e9ger les droits de propri\u00e9t\u00e9 intellectuelle doivent \u00eatre mises en \u0153uvre.", "A.5.33": "Les enregistrements doivent \u00eatre prot\u00e9g\u00e9s contre la perte, la destruction, la falsification, les acc\u00e8s non autoris\u00e9s et la divulgation.", "A.5.34": "L'organisation doit identifier et satisfaire aux exigences relatives \u00e0 la pr\u00e9servation de la confidentialit\u00e9 et \u00e0 la protection des donn\u00e9es personnelles selon la l\u00e9gislation applicable.", "A.5.35": "L'approche de l'organisation en mati\u00e8re de gestion de la s\u00e9curit\u00e9 doit faire l'objet de revues ind\u00e9pendantes \u00e0 intervalles planifi\u00e9s ou lors de changements significatifs.", "A.5.36": "La conformit\u00e9 aux politiques, r\u00e8gles et normes de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 de l'information de l'organisation doit \u00eatre r\u00e9guli\u00e8rement revue.", "A.5.37": "Les proc\u00e9dures d'exploitation des moyens de traitement de l'information doivent \u00eatre document\u00e9es et mises \u00e0 la disposition des utilisateurs qui en ont besoin.", "A.6.1": "Les v\u00e9rifications des ant\u00e9c\u00e9dents du personnel candidat doivent \u00eatre effectu\u00e9es avant l'embauche et \u00e0 intervalles r\u00e9guliers, conform\u00e9ment aux l\u00e9gislations applicables.", "A.6.2": "Les accords contractuels avec le personnel et les contractants doivent pr\u00e9ciser leurs responsabilit\u00e9s et celles de l'organisation en mati\u00e8re de s\u00e9curit\u00e9.", "A.6.3": "Le personnel et les contractants doivent recevoir une sensibilisation, une formation et une \u00e9ducation appropri\u00e9es \u00e0 leurs fonctions, avec des mises \u00e0 jour r\u00e9guli\u00e8res.", "A.6.4": "Un processus disciplinaire formel doit exister et \u00eatre communiqu\u00e9 pour traiter les violations de la politique de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 par le personnel.", "A.6.5": "Les responsabilit\u00e9s et obligations de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 restant applicables apr\u00e8s la fin ou le changement d'emploi doivent \u00eatre d\u00e9finies, communiqu\u00e9es et respect\u00e9es.", "A.6.6": "Les accords de confidentialit\u00e9 ou de non-divulgation refl\u00e9tant les besoins de protection de l'information doivent \u00eatre identifi\u00e9s, document\u00e9s, revu r\u00e9guli\u00e8rement et sign\u00e9s.", "A.6.7": "Des mesures de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 doivent \u00eatre d\u00e9finies et mises en \u0153uvre lorsque le personnel travaille \u00e0 distance afin de prot\u00e9ger les informations consult\u00e9es, trait\u00e9es ou stock\u00e9es.", "A.6.8": "L'organisation doit fournir un m\u00e9canisme permettant au personnel de signaler les \u00e9v\u00e9nements de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 observ\u00e9s ou suspect\u00e9s, de mani\u00e8re confidentielle si n\u00e9cessaire.", "A.7.1": "Des p\u00e9rim\u00e8tres de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 physique doivent \u00eatre d\u00e9finis et utilis\u00e9s pour prot\u00e9ger les zones contenant des informations sensibles et les moyens de traitement.", "A.7.2": "Les zones s\u00e9curis\u00e9es doivent \u00eatre prot\u00e9g\u00e9es par des contr\u00f4les d'entr\u00e9e et des points d'acc\u00e8s appropri\u00e9s assurant que seul le personnel autoris\u00e9 peut y acc\u00e9der.", "A.7.3": "La s\u00e9curit\u00e9 physique des bureaux, salles et \u00e9quipements doit \u00eatre con\u00e7ue et mise en \u0153uvre.", "A.7.4": "Les locaux doivent faire l'objet d'une surveillance physique continue pour d\u00e9tecter et pr\u00e9venir les acc\u00e8s non autoris\u00e9s.", "A.7.5": "Des protections contre les menaces physiques et environnementales (catastrophes naturelles, accidents industriels, attentats) doivent \u00eatre con\u00e7ues et mises en \u0153uvre.", "A.7.6": "Des proc\u00e9dures de travail dans les zones s\u00e9curis\u00e9es doivent \u00eatre con\u00e7ues et mises en \u0153uvre.", "A.7.7": "Des r\u00e8gles de bureau propre pour les papiers et les supports de stockage amovibles, et de verrouillage d'\u00e9cran doivent \u00eatre d\u00e9finies et appliqu\u00e9es.", "A.7.8": "Les \u00e9quipements doivent \u00eatre prot\u00e9g\u00e9s contre les menaces physiques et environnementales, et dispos\u00e9s de mani\u00e8re \u00e0 r\u00e9duire les risques d'acc\u00e8s non autoris\u00e9s.", "A.7.9": "Les actifs hors des locaux doivent \u00eatre prot\u00e9g\u00e9s en tenant compte des diff\u00e9rents risques li\u00e9s au travail hors de ces locaux.", "A.7.10": "Les supports de stockage doivent \u00eatre g\u00e9r\u00e9s tout au long de leur cycle de vie d'acquisition, d'utilisation, de transport et de suppression selon la classification de l'information.", "A.7.11": "Les \u00e9quipements doivent \u00eatre prot\u00e9g\u00e9s contre les d\u00e9faillances d'alimentation \u00e9lectrique et autres perturbations caus\u00e9es par des d\u00e9faillances des services g\u00e9n\u00e9raux.", "A.7.12": "Les c\u00e2bles v\u00e9hiculant des donn\u00e9es ou supportant les services d'information doivent \u00eatre prot\u00e9g\u00e9s contre les interceptions, les interf\u00e9rences ou les dommages.", "A.7.13": "Les \u00e9quipements doivent faire l'objet d'une maintenance correcte pour assurer leur disponibilit\u00e9 et leur int\u00e9grit\u00e9 permanente.", "A.7.14": "Les \u00e9quipements contenant des supports de stockage doivent \u00eatre v\u00e9rifi\u00e9s pour s'assurer que toutes les donn\u00e9es sensibles et les logiciels sous licence ont \u00e9t\u00e9 supprim\u00e9s avant mise au rebut.", "A.8.1": "Des postes de travail utilisateurs non surveill\u00e9s doivent disposer d'une protection appropri\u00e9e : verrouillage automatique, d\u00e9connexion des sessions, protection par mot de passe.", "A.8.2": "L'attribution et l'utilisation de droits d'acc\u00e8s privil\u00e9gi\u00e9s doivent \u00eatre restreintes et g\u00e9r\u00e9es avec rigueur : attribution formelle, revue r\u00e9guli\u00e8re, r\u00e9vocation imm\u00e9diate si inutile.", "A.8.3": "L'acc\u00e8s aux informations et fonctions des applications doit \u00eatre restreint conform\u00e9ment \u00e0 la politique de contr\u00f4le d'acc\u00e8s d\u00e9finie.", "A.8.4": "L'acc\u00e8s en lecture et \u00e9criture au code source, aux outils de d\u00e9veloppement et aux biblioth\u00e8ques logicielles doit \u00eatre g\u00e9r\u00e9 de mani\u00e8re stricte.", "A.8.5": "Des technologies et proc\u00e9dures d'authentification s\u00e9curis\u00e9e doivent \u00eatre mises en \u0153uvre pour contr\u00f4ler les acc\u00e8s aux syst\u00e8mes selon les politiques d\u00e9finies.", "A.8.6": "L'utilisation des ressources doit \u00eatre surveill\u00e9e et des ajustements apport\u00e9s pour r\u00e9pondre aux exigences de capacit\u00e9 pr\u00e9sentes et futures.", "A.8.7": "Une protection contre les logiciels malveillants doit \u00eatre mise en \u0153uvre, tenue \u00e0 jour et soutenue par une sensibilisation appropri\u00e9e des utilisateurs.", "A.8.8": "Les informations sur les vuln\u00e9rabilit\u00e9s techniques des syst\u00e8mes utilis\u00e9s doivent \u00eatre obtenues en temps voulu, l'exposition \u00e9valu\u00e9e et les mesures appropri\u00e9es prises.", "A.8.9": "Les configurations de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 des \u00e9quipements, logiciels et r\u00e9seaux doivent \u00eatre \u00e9tablies, document\u00e9es, mises en \u0153uvre, surveill\u00e9es et revues.", "A.8.10": "Les informations stock\u00e9es dans les syst\u00e8mes, \u00e9quipements ou supports doivent \u00eatre supprim\u00e9es de fa\u00e7on s\u00e9curis\u00e9e lorsqu'elles ne sont plus n\u00e9cessaires.", "A.8.11": "Le masquage des donn\u00e9es doit \u00eatre utilis\u00e9 conform\u00e9ment \u00e0 la politique de contr\u00f4le d'acc\u00e8s et aux exigences l\u00e9gales, notamment pour les donn\u00e9es personnelles.", "A.8.12": "Des mesures de pr\u00e9vention des fuites de donn\u00e9es doivent \u00eatre appliqu\u00e9es aux syst\u00e8mes, r\u00e9seaux et appareils qui traitent, stockent ou transmettent des informations sensibles.", "A.8.13": "Des copies de sauvegarde des informations, logiciels et syst\u00e8mes doivent \u00eatre r\u00e9alis\u00e9es et test\u00e9es r\u00e9guli\u00e8rement conform\u00e9ment \u00e0 une politique de sauvegarde d\u00e9finie.", "A.8.14": "Les moyens de traitement de l'information doivent \u00eatre mis en \u0153uvre avec une redondance suffisante pour satisfaire aux exigences de disponibilit\u00e9.", "A.8.15": "Des journaux enregistrant les activit\u00e9s, exceptions, erreurs et autres \u00e9v\u00e9nements pertinents doivent \u00eatre produits, stock\u00e9s, prot\u00e9g\u00e9s et analys\u00e9s.", "A.8.16": "Les r\u00e9seaux, syst\u00e8mes et applications doivent faire l'objet d'une surveillance pour d\u00e9tecter les comportements anormaux et prendre les mesures appropri\u00e9es.", "A.8.17": "Les horloges des syst\u00e8mes de traitement de l'information utilis\u00e9s par l'organisation doivent \u00eatre synchronis\u00e9es avec des sources de temps de r\u00e9f\u00e9rence approuv\u00e9es.", "A.8.18": "L'utilisation de programmes utilitaires susceptibles de contourner les contr\u00f4les syst\u00e8me et applicatifs doit \u00eatre restreinte et surveill\u00e9e de mani\u00e8re stricte.", "A.8.19": "Des proc\u00e9dures et mesures pour contr\u00f4ler l'installation de logiciels sur les syst\u00e8mes en exploitation doivent \u00eatre d\u00e9finies et mises en \u0153uvre.", "A.8.20": "Les r\u00e9seaux et \u00e9quipements r\u00e9seau doivent \u00eatre s\u00e9curis\u00e9s, g\u00e9r\u00e9s et contr\u00f4l\u00e9s pour prot\u00e9ger les informations dans les syst\u00e8mes et les applications.", "A.8.21": "Les m\u00e9canismes de s\u00e9curit\u00e9, niveaux de service et exigences de gestion de tous les services r\u00e9seau doivent \u00eatre identifi\u00e9s, mis en \u0153uvre et surveill\u00e9s.", "A.8.22": "L'acc\u00e8s \u00e0 des sites Web externes doit \u00eatre g\u00e9r\u00e9 pour r\u00e9duire l'exposition aux contenus malveillants. Des filtres de cat\u00e9gories URL doivent \u00eatre mis en place.", "A.8.23": "Les groupes de services d'information, les utilisateurs et les syst\u00e8mes d'information doivent \u00eatre cloisonn\u00e9s dans les r\u00e9seaux de l'organisation.", "A.8.24": "Des r\u00e8gles relatives \u00e0 l'utilisation appropri\u00e9e de la cryptographie, y compris la gestion des cl\u00e9s, doivent \u00eatre d\u00e9finies et mises en \u0153uvre.", "A.8.25": "Des r\u00e8gles de d\u00e9veloppement s\u00e9curis\u00e9 des logiciels et des syst\u00e8mes doivent \u00eatre \u00e9tablies et appliqu\u00e9es (SDLC s\u00e9curis\u00e9, revues de code, tests de s\u00e9curit\u00e9).", "A.8.26": "Les exigences de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 de l'information doivent \u00eatre identifi\u00e9es et pr\u00e9cis\u00e9es lors du d\u00e9veloppement ou de l'acquisition de nouvelles applications.", "A.8.27": "Des principes d'ing\u00e9nierie de syst\u00e8mes s\u00e9curis\u00e9s doivent \u00eatre \u00e9tablis, document\u00e9s, maintenus et appliqu\u00e9s \u00e0 toute activit\u00e9 de mise en \u0153uvre de syst\u00e8mes d'information.", "A.8.28": "Des principes de codage s\u00e9curis\u00e9 doivent \u00eatre appliqu\u00e9s au d\u00e9veloppement logiciel (OWASP, revues de code, analyse statique, tests de s\u00e9curit\u00e9).", "A.8.29": "Des processus de tests de s\u00e9curit\u00e9 doivent \u00eatre d\u00e9finis et mis en \u0153uvre dans le cycle de d\u00e9veloppement, incluant les tests unitaires, d'int\u00e9gration et de p\u00e9n\u00e9tration.", "A.8.30": "L'organisation doit superviser, revoir et auditer les activit\u00e9s de d\u00e9veloppement de syst\u00e8mes externalis\u00e9es.", "A.8.31": "Les environnements de d\u00e9veloppement, de test et de production doivent \u00eatre s\u00e9par\u00e9s et s\u00e9curis\u00e9s pour pr\u00e9venir les acc\u00e8s non autoris\u00e9s et prot\u00e9ger l'environnement de production.", "A.8.32": "Les changements apport\u00e9s aux moyens de traitement et aux syst\u00e8mes d'information doivent \u00eatre soumis \u00e0 des proc\u00e9dures formelles de gestion des changements.", "A.8.33": "Les informations de test doivent \u00eatre s\u00e9lectionn\u00e9es, prot\u00e9g\u00e9es et g\u00e9r\u00e9es de fa\u00e7on appropri\u00e9e pour \u00e9viter l'utilisation de donn\u00e9es de production sensibles.", "A.8.34": "Les tests d'audit et autres activit\u00e9s d'assurance impliquant l'\u00e9valuation des syst\u00e8mes en exploitation doivent \u00eatre planifi\u00e9s, convenus et contr\u00f4l\u00e9s."}, anssi_en: {"1": "Organise regular information security training for technical teams (administrators, developers, operators). Cover current threats, security tools and internal procedures.", "2": "Implement periodic awareness actions for all employees: phishing recognition, password management, incident reporting, IT resource usage.", "3": "Maintain an up-to-date IS map: networks, systems, applications, data flows. Review it upon any significant change and protect its confidentiality.", "4": "Keep a comprehensive, up-to-date inventory of all hardware and software assets. Assign a responsible owner to each asset.", "5": "Define information classification levels (e.g. public, internal, confidential, secret). Identify servers hosting the most sensitive data and apply enhanced protection measures.", "6": "Identify all privileged accounts (local administrators, domain, service, application). Regularly audit and clean up this inventory; remove obsolete accounts.", "7": "Formalise and apply access management procedures for arrivals (account creation), transfers (rights update) and departures (access removal, equipment recovery).", "8": "Restrict access to administration interfaces and tools to formally authorised personnel only. Maintain an authorisation list and review it regularly.", "9": "Define a password policy (minimum length >= 12 characters, complexity, renewal, history) and enforce it technically on all systems.", "10": "Never store passwords in cleartext. Use robust hashing functions with salt (bcrypt, Argon2, PBKDF2). Regularly audit authentication databases.", "11": "Deploy multi-factor authentication (MFA) for access to critical resources, privileged accounts and all remote access to the IS.", "12": "Prohibit cleartext passwords in configuration files, scripts, source code or databases. Use secrets vaults.", "13": "Systematically change default credentials on all network equipment, servers, applications and databases before commissioning.", "14": "Centralise authentication via a directory (Active Directory, LDAP, SSO) to reduce local account proliferation and facilitate rights management.", "15": "Apply the principle of least privilege: grant each user, application or service only the rights strictly necessary for their functions. Review rights regularly.", "16": "Apply security updates to all software (OS, browsers, plugins, business applications) within timeframes adapted to vulnerability criticality.", "17": "Define and apply a baseline security configuration (CIS benchmark or equivalent) on all workstations: disable unnecessary services, enable local firewall, enable disk encryption.", "18": "Encrypt sensitive data stored on workstations (BitLocker, FileVault or equivalent). Protect encryption keys with an appropriate mechanism.", "19": "Deploy and maintain an up-to-date malware protection solution (antivirus, EDR) across the entire fleet. Enable centralised alert supervision.", "20": "Define a removable media usage policy: prohibit unauthorised media, control transfers, scan external media before use.", "21": "Segment the network into trust zones (DMZ, administration network, user network, OT...) and filter inter-zone traffic with firewalls or ACLs based on the need-to-know principle.", "22": "Use WPA2-Enterprise or WPA3 for professional Wi-Fi networks. Isolate guest Wi-Fi networks from the internal network. Disable obsolete protocols (WEP, WPA).", "23": "Ban unencrypted protocols (Telnet, FTP, HTTP, SNMPv1/v2) and replace them with their secure equivalents (SSH, SFTP/FTPS, HTTPS, SNMPv3).", "24": "Implement a filtering proxy, application firewall and gateway antivirus protection to supervise and filter inbound and outbound Internet traffic.", "25": "Contractually and technically govern interconnections with partners: encrypted VPN, strong authentication, flows limited to strict necessity, regular supervision and audit.", "26": "Govern remote access via VPN with strong authentication (MFA). Log all sessions. Regularly review remote access rights and revoke unused access.", "27": "Deploy a network flow monitoring solution (SIEM, IDS/IPS, NetFlow) to detect abnormal behaviour, data exfiltration and intrusion attempts.", "28": "Use workstations dedicated exclusively to administration tasks, without Internet access or office messaging. These workstations must not be used for routine activities.", "29": "Restrict and secure remote access tools (RDP, SSH, third-party tools): access limited to authorised administrators only, strong encryption, logging, MFA.", "30": "Isolate the administration network in a dedicated VLAN or segment, physically or logically separated from user networks and accessible only from administration workstations.", "31": "Enable logging of all administration operations (connections, commands, configuration changes). Store logs in a space with integrity protection.", "32": "Grant administration rights to the strict minimum necessary. Use temporary privilege elevation (sudo, PAM) rather than permanent high-privilege accounts.", "33": "Protect mobile devices against loss and theft: security cable, password-protected startup, disk encryption enabled, loss reporting procedure.", "34": "Fully encrypt the disk of mobile devices (BitLocker, FileVault, VeraCrypt). Ensure encryption is active before any use outside the premises.", "35": "Require the use of a corporate VPN for any access to the IS from outside. Disable direct connections without VPN. Check workstation compliance before connection (NAC).", "36": "Define a formal update policy specifying application timeframes by criticality level (CVSS >= 9: < 72h, CVSS 7-9: < 7d, others: < 30d) and testing procedures.", "37": "Identify end-of-life software and systems (EOL/EOS). Plan and budget migration before vendor support ends. Isolate non-migratable systems in the meantime.", "38": "Apply critical security patches within the timeframes defined by the update policy. Implement a patch management process with testing, deployment and verification.", "39": "Enable and centralise logs from critical equipment (AD, firewalls, servers, applications). Define retention period (>= 1 year recommended). Protect log integrity.", "40": "Define and apply a backup policy (3-2-1 rule: 3 copies, 2 different media, 1 off-site). Regularly test restorations. Protect backups against ransomware.", "41": "Conduct regular security audits (penetration tests, configuration reviews, code audits) by PASSI-qualified providers. Track and remediate identified vulnerabilities.", "42": "Officially appoint a security officer or CISO responsible for IS security. Define their scope of responsibilities, allocate necessary resources and make them known to all employees."}, iso_en: {"4.1": "The organization shall determine external and internal issues that are relevant to its purpose and that affect its ability to achieve the intended outcome(s) of its ISMS.", "4.2": "The organization shall determine interested parties that are relevant to the ISMS and the requirements of these interested parties.", "4.3": "The organization shall determine the boundaries and applicability of the ISMS to establish its scope, considering the issues, requirements and interfaces.", "4.4": "The organization shall establish, implement, maintain and continually improve an information security management system, including the processes needed and their interactions.", "5.1": "Top management shall demonstrate leadership and commitment with respect to the ISMS: define the policy, ensure integration into business processes, provide resources, communicate the importance.", "5.2": "Top management shall establish an information security policy appropriate to the purpose of the organization, including objectives, a commitment to compliance and continual improvement. It shall be documented, communicated and available.", "5.3": "Top management shall ensure that responsibilities and authorities for roles relevant to information security are assigned and communicated within the organization.", "6.1.1": "When planning for the ISMS, the organization shall determine the risks and opportunities that need to be addressed to ensure the ISMS can achieve its intended outcomes.", "6.1.2": "The organization shall define and apply an information security risk assessment process: acceptance criteria, reproducible methodology, risk identification, analysis and evaluation.", "6.1.3": "The organization shall define and apply an information security risk treatment process: select treatment options, determine necessary controls, produce a Statement of Applicability.", "6.2": "The organization shall establish information security objectives at relevant functions and levels. They shall be measurable, consistent with the policy, communicated and updated.", "6.3": "When the organization determines the need for changes to the ISMS, they shall be planned and carried out in a controlled manner.", "7.1": "The organization shall determine and provide the resources needed for the establishment, implementation, maintenance and continual improvement of the ISMS.", "7.2": "The organization shall determine the necessary competence of persons doing work affecting information security performance, ensure they are competent, and retain evidence.", "7.3": "Persons doing work under the organization's control shall be aware of the information security policy, their contribution to ISMS effectiveness, and the implications of non-conformity.", "7.4": "The organization shall determine the need for internal and external communications relevant to the ISMS: what to communicate, when, to whom, how.", "7.5.1": "The organization's ISMS shall include documented information required by this standard and determined necessary for ISMS effectiveness.", "7.5.2": "When creating and updating documented information, the organization shall ensure appropriate identification, format, review and approval.", "7.5.3": "Documented information shall be controlled to ensure it is available, adequately protected, distributed, stored, retained and disposed of appropriately.", "8.1": "The organization shall plan, implement and control the processes needed to meet information security requirements and to realize the actions determined in planning.", "8.2": "The organization shall perform information security risk assessments at planned intervals or when significant changes are proposed or occur.", "8.3": "The organization shall implement the information security risk treatment plan and retain documented information on the results of risk treatment.", "9.1": "The organization shall evaluate information security performance and ISMS effectiveness: determine what to monitor and measure, the methods, frequency and responsibilities.", "9.2": "The organization shall conduct internal audits at planned intervals to provide information on whether the ISMS conforms to its own requirements and to the standard.", "9.3": "Top management shall review the ISMS at planned intervals to ensure its continuing suitability, adequacy and effectiveness.", "10.1": "The organization shall continually improve the suitability, adequacy and effectiveness of the ISMS.", "10.2": "When a nonconformity occurs, the organization shall react, evaluate actions needed to eliminate its cause, implement corrective actions and verify their effectiveness.", "A.5.1": "Information security policies, approved by management, published and communicated to relevant personnel and interested parties, shall be defined and reviewed at planned intervals.", "A.5.2": "Information security roles and responsibilities shall be defined and allocated in accordance with established policies.", "A.5.3": "Conflicting duties and areas of responsibility shall be segregated to reduce risks of unauthorized modification or misuse of assets.", "A.5.4": "Management shall require all personnel to apply information security in accordance with the established policies, rules and procedures.", "A.5.5": "Appropriate contacts with relevant authorities (regulators, law enforcement, fire brigade, etc.) shall be established and maintained.", "A.5.6": "Appropriate contacts with special interest groups or other specialist security forums and professional associations shall be established and maintained.", "A.5.7": "Information relating to information security threats shall be collected and analysed to produce threat intelligence.", "A.5.8": "Information security shall be integrated into project management throughout the project life cycle.", "A.5.9": "An inventory of information and other associated assets, including their owners, shall be developed and maintained.", "A.5.10": "Rules for the acceptable use and procedures for handling information and other associated assets shall be identified, documented and implemented.", "A.5.11": "Personnel and other interested parties as appropriate shall return all organizational assets in their possession upon change or termination of their employment, contract or agreement.", "A.5.12": "Information shall be classified according to the information security needs of the organization based on confidentiality, integrity, availability and relevant interested party requirements.", "A.5.13": "An appropriate set of procedures for information labelling shall be developed and implemented in accordance with the information classification scheme adopted by the organization.", "A.5.14": "Rules, procedures or agreements for information transfer shall be in place for all types of transfer facilities within the organization and between the organization and other parties.", "A.5.15": "Rules to control physical and logical access to information and other associated assets shall be established and implemented based on business and information security requirements.", "A.5.16": "The full life cycle of identities shall be managed.", "A.5.17": "Allocation and management of authentication information shall be controlled by a management process.", "A.5.18": "Access rights to information and other associated assets shall be provisioned, reviewed, modified and removed in accordance with the organization's topic-specific policy on and rules for access control.", "A.5.19": "Processes and procedures shall be defined and implemented to manage the information security risks associated with the use of supplier's products or services.", "A.5.20": "Relevant information security requirements shall be established and agreed with each supplier based on the type of supplier relationship.", "A.5.21": "Processes and procedures shall be defined and implemented to manage the information security risks associated with the ICT products and services supply chain.", "A.5.22": "The organization shall regularly monitor, review, evaluate and manage change in supplier information security practices and service delivery.", "A.5.23": "Processes for acquisition, use, management and exit from cloud services shall be established in accordance with the organization's information security requirements.", "A.5.24": "The organization shall plan and prepare for managing information security incidents by defining, establishing and communicating information security incident management processes, roles and responsibilities.", "A.5.25": "The organization shall assess information security events and decide whether they are to be categorized as information security incidents.", "A.5.26": "Information security incidents shall be responded to in accordance with the documented procedures.", "A.5.27": "Knowledge gained from information security incidents shall be used to strengthen and improve the information security controls.", "A.5.28": "The organization shall establish and implement procedures for the identification, collection, acquisition and preservation of evidence related to information security events.", "A.5.29": "The organization shall plan how to maintain its information security at an appropriate level during disruption.", "A.5.30": "ICT readiness shall be planned, implemented, maintained and tested based on business continuity objectives and ICT continuity requirements.", "A.5.31": "Legal, statutory, regulatory and contractual requirements relevant to information security and the organization's approach to meet these requirements shall be identified, documented and kept up to date.", "A.5.32": "The organization shall protect intellectual property rights.", "A.5.33": "Records shall be protected from loss, destruction, falsification, unauthorized access and unauthorized release.", "A.5.34": "The organization shall identify and meet the requirements of privacy and protection of PII as applicable.", "A.5.35": "The organization's approach to managing information security and its implementation shall be independently reviewed at planned intervals or when significant changes occur.", "A.5.36": "Compliance with the organization's established information security policy, topic-specific policies, rules and standards shall be regularly reviewed.", "A.5.37": "Operating procedures shall be documented and made available to personnel who need them.", "A.6.1": "Information security screening shall be carried out on all candidates for employment prior to joining the organization and on an ongoing basis.", "A.6.2": "Contractual agreements shall state the employees' and the organization's responsibilities for information security.", "A.6.3": "All personnel of the organization and relevant interested parties shall receive appropriate information security awareness, education and training and regular updates of the organization's information security policy.", "A.6.4": "A disciplinary process shall be formalized and communicated to take actions against personnel and other relevant interested parties who have committed an information security policy violation.", "A.6.5": "Information security responsibilities and duties that remain valid after termination or change of employment shall be defined, enforced and communicated to relevant personnel and other interested parties.", "A.6.6": "Confidentiality or non-disclosure agreements reflecting the organization's needs for the protection of information shall be identified, documented, regularly reviewed and signed by personnel and other relevant interested parties.", "A.6.7": "Security measures shall be implemented when personnel are working remotely to protect information accessed, processed or stored outside the organization's premises.", "A.6.8": "A mechanism shall be established for personnel to report observed or suspected information security events through appropriate channels in a timely manner.", "A.7.1": "Security perimeters shall be defined and used to protect areas that contain information and other associated assets.", "A.7.2": "Secure areas shall be protected by appropriate entry controls and access points.", "A.7.3": "Physical security for offices, rooms and facilities shall be designed and implemented.", "A.7.4": "Continuous monitoring for unauthorized physical access shall be devised and implemented.", "A.7.5": "Protections against physical and environmental threats, such as natural disasters and other intentional or unintentional physical threats to infrastructure, shall be designed and implemented.", "A.7.6": "Security measures for working in secure areas shall be designed and implemented.", "A.7.7": "Verify clear desks for papers and removable storage media and clear screens for information processing facilities.", "A.7.8": "Equipment shall be sited securely and protected.", "A.7.9": "Assets off-premises shall be protected.", "A.7.10": "Storage media shall be managed through their life cycle of acquisition, use, transportation and disposal in accordance with the organization's classification scheme and handling requirements.", "A.7.11": "Supporting utilities, such as electricity, telecommunications, water supply, shall be protected from interception, interference or damage.", "A.7.12": "Cables carrying power, data or supporting information services shall be protected from interception, interference or damage.", "A.7.13": "Equipment shall be maintained correctly to ensure availability, integrity and confidentiality of information.", "A.7.14": "Items of equipment containing storage media shall be verified to ensure that any sensitive data and licensed software has been removed or securely overwritten prior to disposal or re-use.", "A.8.1": "An inventory of information and other associated assets, including owners, shall be identified.", "A.8.2": "Information and other associated assets associated with information and information processing facilities shall be identified and an inventory of these assets shall be drawn up and maintained.", "A.8.3": "Rules for the acceptable use of information and other associated assets and for information processing facilities shall be identified, documented and implemented.", "A.8.4": "Access to information and other associated assets shall be managed through a topic-specific policy.", "A.8.5": "Multi-factor authentication methods shall be applied for access to information systems based on the organization's authentication policy.", "A.8.6": "Information systems capacity shall be managed to meet current and expected capacity demands.", "A.8.7": "Protection against malware shall be implemented and supported by appropriate user awareness.", "A.8.8": "Information about technical vulnerabilities of information systems in use shall be obtained, the organization's exposure to such vulnerabilities shall be evaluated and appropriate measures shall be taken.", "A.8.9": "Configurations, including security configurations, of hardware, software, services and networks shall be established, documented, implemented, monitored and reviewed.", "A.8.10": "Information stored in information systems, devices or in any other storage media shall be deleted when no longer required.", "A.8.11": "Data masking shall be used in accordance with the organization's topic-specific policy on access control and other related topic-specific policies, and business requirements, taking applicable legislation into consideration.", "A.8.12": "Data leakage prevention measures shall be applied to systems, networks and any other devices that process, store or transmit sensitive information.", "A.8.13": "Backup copies of information, software and systems shall be maintained and regularly tested in accordance with the agreed topic-specific policy on backup.", "A.8.14": "Information processing facilities shall be implemented with redundancy sufficient to meet availability requirements.", "A.8.15": "Logs that record activities, exceptions, faults and other relevant events shall be produced, stored, protected and analysed.", "A.8.16": "Networks, systems and applications shall be monitored for anomalous behaviour and appropriate actions taken to evaluate potential information security events.", "A.8.17": "The clocks of information processing systems used by the organization shall be synchronized to approved time sources.", "A.8.18": "The use of utility programs that might be capable of overriding system and application controls shall be restricted and tightly controlled.", "A.8.19": "Procedures and measures shall be implemented to securely manage software installation on operational systems.", "A.8.20": "Networks and network devices shall be secured, managed and controlled to protect information in systems and applications.", "A.8.21": "Security mechanisms, service levels, and service requirements of network services shall be identified, implemented and monitored.", "A.8.22": "Groups of information services, users and information systems shall be segregated in the organization's networks.", "A.8.23": "Web filtering: Access to external websites shall be managed to reduce exposure to malicious content.", "A.8.24": "Rules for the effective use of cryptography, including cryptographic key management, shall be defined and implemented.", "A.8.25": "Rules for the secure development of software and systems shall be established and applied.", "A.8.26": "Information security requirements shall be identified, specified and managed throughout the development life cycle of information systems.", "A.8.27": "Secure system architecture and engineering principles shall be established, documented, maintained and applied to any information system development activities.", "A.8.28": "Secure coding principles shall be applied to software development.", "A.8.29": "Security testing processes shall be defined and implemented in the development life cycle.", "A.8.30": "The organization shall direct, monitor, and review the activities related to outsourced system development.", "A.8.31": "Development, testing and production environments shall be separated and secured.", "A.8.32": "Change control procedures and change management tools shall be applied to changes made to production processing facilities and systems.", "A.8.33": "Test information shall be appropriately selected, protected and managed.", "A.8.34": "Audit tests and other assurance activities involving assessment of operational systems shall be planned, agreed and controlled."}};
